*Scenario:*
 # Have two remotes, {{origin}} and {{foo}}
 # Have a remote branch {{foo.bar}} and a local branch {{bar}} that tracks {{foo.bar}}
 # Check out local branch {{bar}}
 # Hit the "Push" button in the toolbar to open the push dialog

*Expected outcome:*
 * Remote {{foo}} is selected by default, because the current branch tracks a branch on that remote, and the branch itself is selected for push to the tracked branch.

*Actual outcome:*
 * Remote {{origin}} is selected by default, and since there's no corresponding {{bar}} branch on that remote, the local branch is *not* selected for push; remote needs to be manually selected on every single push.

Pushing via the context menu on the branch itself selects the correct remote, but it is about as inconvenient as having to select the remote every time.
